  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Accelerated Action against Plague in Madagascar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Small-scale/epid.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Malagasy Red Cross Society (MRCS) is scaling up its response to the exceptional pulmonary plague outbreak working with the Malagasy Ministry of Health and other partners in coordinated response. Through the activities outlined in this proposal, plague-related burden of disease in affected communities is reduced through community engagement, behaviour change communication, and provision of psychosocial support. This will be done through the following activities:- Strengthening community engagement in epidemic areas and their surroundings to promote early alert and action;- Promotion of health in the community through a communication plan to educate the community about theepidemic risk; its prevention, and the mobilization for the fight against the epidemic;- Providing psychosocial support to confirmed cases, contact cases and affected families as well as after-action support to community volunteers</narrative>
  </description>
